review_blob: This is a standard, go-to beer for me.  Its smooth, not cloyingly citrusy, is a nice golden hue, and has the cloudiness one would associate with a Belgian white.  Is it a revelation?  No.  But when I want to settle in at night with a beer, this is an option that I enjoy.
Picked up this one on suggestion of the girlfriend.  Citrusy without being annoying, hoppy on the back palate.  The appearance is nice and unfiltered and overall a solid brew.
